title: FSIS Issues Public Health Alert for Frozen, Cooked Diced Poultry Products Due to Possible Listeria Contamination
summary: Editor’s note: Details of this public health alert were updated on May 25, 2021 to reflect a change on product distribution dates and to include a list of distribution locations. WASHINGTON, May 24, 2021 - The U.S. Department of Agriculture’s Food Safety and Inspection Service...
impacted_products: 4-lb. plastic bags containing “FULLY COOKED CHICKEN MEAT ¾ DICED WHITE” with code 13530, Est. number P-18237, and pack dates of “01/25/2021” and “01/26/2021.”
4-lb. plastic bags containing “FULLY COOKED CHICKEN MEAT DARK/WHITE ¾ DICED” with code 16598, Est. number P-45638, and pack dates “24/MAR/2021” and “23/MAR/2021.”
